title: Lima city Highlights ( All included! )
description: Sometimes called the Galapagos of Peru, the Ballestas Islands, south of Lima, are home to penguins, sea lions, and other sea birds and marine mammals. This full-day private tour is exclusively for you and your group and delivers the chance to see this wildlife by boat. Then explore the dunes and seashore of the picturesque Paracas National Reserve (parts of the movie Don't Look Up were filmed here) by vehicle before returning to Lima.
all_descriptions: Sometimes called the Galapagos of Peru, the Ballestas Islands, south of Lima, are home to penguins, sea lions, and other sea birds and marine mammals. This full-day private tour is exclusively for you and your group and delivers the chance to see this wildlife by boat. Then explore the dunes and seashore of the picturesque Paracas National Reserve (parts of the movie Don't Look Up were filmed here) by vehicle before returning to Lima.

ItineraryThis is a typical itinerary for this productStop At:Huaca Pucllana, Calle General Borgono s/n, cuadra 8, Lima 15074 PeruTendremos una vista panoramica y explicacion de la historia de este lugar sagrado conocido como "Huaca"Duration: 20 minutesStop At:Barranco, Lima PeruEl distrito "bohemio" de Lima nos espera junto con el "Puente de los suspiros" y su tradicional Cantautora peruana Chabuca Granda, conoscamos juntos la iglesia la hermita y de la nueva zona de murales y graffitis de la ciudad.Duration: 30 minutesStop At:Fisherman's Wharf, RXMC+H67, Cto. de Playas, Chorrillos 15063, PeruConosca a personas locales y escuche de ellos sus historias y vea de cerca los peces de la pesca del día, aprenda sobre los peces de la costa peruana y disfrute de la vista del lugarDuration: 30 minutesStop At:El Parque del Amor, Malecon Cisneros 18, Lima PeruDisfrute de unas hermosas fotografias en este parque íconico de la ciudad de Lima, en el distrito de Miraflores.Duration: 20 minutesStop At:Mercado nro 1 de Surquillo, Av. Paseo de la Republica, Lima PeruQue mejor de disfrutar de nuestro plato bandera el "Cebiche peruano" en un mercado local, aprendiendo más sobre las frutas , verduras y conociendo de cerca nuestra cultura gastronomica.Duration: 1 hourStop At:Museo Convento San Francisco y Catacumbas, Jiron Ancash, Lima 15001 PeruDescubre Las catacumbas subterraneas de la ciudad de Lima, aquí encontraremos más de 2 mil recintos el cual fue en su tiempo el mas grande cementerio de LimaDuration: 1 minuteStop At:Plaza de Armas (Plaza Mayor), Jr. Junin and Jr. Carabaya, Lima PeruLa plaza mayor de Lima nos invita a conocerla junto con la Catedral de Lima y el imponente Palacio de Gobierno peruano, junto con sus balcones e historia de la mano de su guia turistico local.Duration: 20 minutesStop At:Plaza San Martin, Av. Nicolas de Pierola cdra. 9, Lima 15001 PeruFinalmente visite la segunda plaza más importante de Lima, la plaza san martin junto con su "LLAMA" y anecdotas que su guia le contará.Duration: 20 minutesStop At:Morro Solar, Chorillos, Lima PeruOur first visit will be to one of the highest points of the city, located in the Chorrillos district to head towards the historic “Morro Solar” (300 meters above sea level), where a privileged view will be waiting for us and we will be able to learn about the history of this place. and Peru in general.Duration: 20 minutesStop At:Jiron de La Union, Union Street, Lima PeruThis is an unmissable street! You will have a panoramic view and appreciate very beautiful architecture, large wooden balconies, impressive rock engravings and monumental churches and religious altars. The local atmosphere, shops, chicken restaurants and local music will make your day very exciting, happy and surely interesting!Duration: 20 minutesStop At:Presidential Palace (Palacio de Gobierno), Plaza de Armas Zocalo, Lima 15001 PeruWe will have a panoramic view of one of the most important houses in the entire country accompanied by a good and rich explanation. Our president lives and works here! Plus, this is where the changing of the guard takes place every day! Let's enjoy great architecture and a place full of history!Duration: 20 minutesStop At:Pasaje Santa Rosa, Pje. Sta. Rosa, Lima, PeruLovely street where locals go to enjoy their day, you usually find temporary exhibitions there, a comfortable atmosphere with an always fresh breeze in the air. This place hides the MOST IMPORTANT sacred rock for the natives still living, this sacred place is still used to make offerings and payments to the gods like mother earth and the natives of Peru came here to do different types of rituals, including dances to keep your culture and energy alive. Good sacred place to go and learn!Duration: 5 minutes

reviews.title: Ne pas manquer les îles ballestas
reviews.text: La visite des îles ballestas se fait uniquement en bateau , on ne peut pas en descendre mais c’est superbe , en plus, le bateau tourne pour que tout le monde puisse prendre des photos, on a vu beaucoup de loup de mer, pleins d’oiseaux, les pingouins, seulement dans l’eau ....Par contre, un peu déçu par la réserve Paracas, les paysages sont magnifiques mais c’est un peu au pas de course, le repas n’est pas compris mais on vous dépose dans un restaurant .. avec l’attente de la préparation, nous avons mangé notre plat à toute vitesse . Un conseil , amener vous de quoi grignoter et profitez de cette pause pour vous promener et prendre des photos ( il y a pleins de pélicans au port)
